Package com.buschmais.xo.api

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CompositeObject
    Defines an interface which is transparently implemented by all composite instances created by the XOManager.
    Example<T>
    An example to be used for XOManager.find(Example, Class).
    Query<T>
    Defines a query using a fluent API.
    Query.Result<T>
    Defines the result of a query.
    Query.Result.CompositeRowObject
    Defines the interface which is implemented by all instances contained in a ResultIterable and which allows access to a column in a row.
    ResultIterable<T>
    An Iterable which allows retrieving a single result.
    ResultIterator<T>
    An Iterator which extends AutoCloseable and Closeable.
    XOManager
    Defines methods to manage the lifecycle of property instances, query execution and transaction management.
    XOManager.MigrationStrategy<T,M>
    Defines the interface of strategies for migration between different composite object types.
    XOManagerFactory
    Defines the factory interfaces for XOManager instances.
    XOTransaction
    Defines the interface for XOManager transactions.
    XOTransaction.Synchronization
    Defines a transaction lifecycle callback which can be registered.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ConcurrencyMode
    Created by dimahler on 1/14/14.
    Transaction.TransactionAttribute
    Defines the supported transaction attributes .
    ValidationMode
    Defines the supported instance validation modes.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    XOException
    The exception thrown by the XO implementation.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    Transaction
    Defines the annotation to be used for declarative transaction demarcation.
